const intro = [
  "A septic system is one of the most expensive things in your home to get wrong. A full pump-out runs $300–$500 or more, and a genuine backup can cost thousands — so a few dollars a month of the right treatment is cheap insurance. The catch: not every product does what it claims, and some do very little at all.",
  "A good treatment keeps the living bacteria in your tank healthy, so they break down solids, grease, and paper instead of letting them build into sludge. The best ones also tackle the smell — the rotten-egg odor that means anaerobic bacteria have taken over. To rank these, we compared how each product works, its verified customer ratings and review volume, value per treatment, and the strength of its guarantee.",
  "One honest note up front: no treatment replaces periodic pumping — they extend the time between pumps and keep the system healthy, they don't make it maintenance-free. Below are the septic treatments actually worth your money in 2026, ranked by our <a href='/how-we-rate/'>Insider Score</a>.",
];

const deepDive = {
  heading: "Why Septifix Is Our #1 Pick",
  body: [
    "Most septic treatments do one job: add bacteria and enzymes to digest solids. Septifix does that — with 14 strains of aerobic bacteria — but it adds a second mechanism most competitors don't have. Each tablet releases oxygen as it dissolves, which directly attacks the anaerobic conditions that cause the rotten-egg smell. If odor is your main complaint, that oxygen-release step is the meaningful difference, and it's why we rank it first for complete, hands-off maintenance.",
    "The practical experience is the other reason it tops the list. It's a single drop-in tablet once a month — no measuring, no pouring powder, no mess. Three tablets to start, then one a month keeps the system topped up. For a lot of people, 'set a monthly reminder and forget it' is the treatment plan that actually gets followed.",
    "We're upfront about the trade-offs: Septifix costs more per dose than a powder like Rid-X, and it's sold online only rather than on a store shelf. What tips it to #1 is the combination — the oxygen-plus-bacteria formula, the convenience, and a genuine 60-day money-back guarantee that most shelf products don't offer. If you'd rather optimize purely for price and a decades-long track record, our Best Value pick, Rid-X, is the smart choice and we'd happily recommend it.",
  ],
};

